HEADWORD: chagrined
<hw>chagrined</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>feeling vexed, especially due to
feeling inferior or unworthy and hence embarrassed; <as>as,
<ex>chagrined</ex> at the poor sales of his book</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> embarrassed, mortified.</syn>⟦br⟧
